# Runtime Framework (Mandatory)

- Treat `ElectronApp/` as frontend control console only; do not place VPN engine logic in renderer/main process business code.
- Treat `core/cmd/waterayd` as long-running backend daemon/service that stays alive after UI exits.
- Route all runtime mutations through control-plane APIs (IPC/HTTP); UI sends command requests and renders returned snapshots.
- Keep core as source of truth for subscriptions, groups, rules, selected group/node, connection stage, traffic stats, and runtime config.
- Limit frontend persistence to UI preferences only (locale/theme/window state/table-layout preferences).
- Keep control schema evolution backward-compatible; additive changes must not break older UI clients.
- Platform runtime shape:
  - Windows/macOS/Linux: daemon or system service.
  - Android: `VpnService` + foreground service.
  - iOS: Network Extension (`Packet Tunnel`) runtime.
- If a feature crosses runtime boundaries, fix architecture first, then implement feature behavior.

## Example

```text
BAD: Electron renderer parses subscriptions and writes runtime routing state as authoritative source.
GOOD: Electron sends import/apply request -> core parses/persists -> renderer only displays state snapshot.
```
